Fri May 29 12:57:47 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Update to version 4.0.0:
  * New md-workbench benchmark (now shipped alongside ior and
    mdtest)
  * New/rewritten S3, PMDK, CHFS, AIO and BFS backends,
    GPUDirect Storage support, CSV output and extensive mdtest
    correctness fixes (see NEWS for the full list)
- Add ior-4.0.0-option-c23-fp.patch: fix a function-pointer
  call rejected by gcc 15 under C23 (fixed in upstream git)
- Disable the RADOS backend: it is broken in the 4.0.0 release
  (src/aiori-RADOS.c was not ported to the new AIORI API);
  this also drops the librbd-devel BuildRequires and the arch
  restriction
- Drop unused libs3-devel BuildRequires (the S3 backend was
  never enabled)
- Strip a bogus relative RUNPATH (check/lib64) from the
  installed binaries

-------------------------------------------------------------------
